title: Umpqua men tie for 25th at NJCAA Championship; Clackamas wins title
title_page: Umpqua men tie for 25th at NJCAA Championship; Clackamas wins title
maintext:
COUNCIL BLUFFS, Iowa — The Clackamas men won the team title Saturday in the National Junior College Athletic Association Championships at the Mid-America Center.
Elijah Ozuna (141 pounds) and Trajan Hurd (174) captured individual titles for the Cougars of Oregon City, who compiled 176.5 points. Clackamas got runner-up finishes from Joel Romero (157) and Joey Daniel (197) and thirds from Zeth Brower (125) and Mason McDaniel (165).
Northeast Oklahoma finished second with 152 points, with Iowa Central in third (125.5) and Northwest Kansas in fourth (109.5). Umpqua tied for 25th (14.5).
Nathan Kiddoo (125) went 3-2 for the Riverhawks in the tournament. Also representing UCC were Sawyer Myres (141), Garrett Russell (149), Braydon Wright (157) and Adam Lamb (285).
